<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="507" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d507">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Moscow Embassy Files: Lot F–96</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The People’s Commissar for Foreign Affairs of the
                                Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Molotov</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the American
                                Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Standley</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-02">2 August
                                1942</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Ambassador</hi>: Kindly transmit the following
                            answer of the President of the Council of People’s Commissars of the
                            USSR J. V. Stalin to the President’s message under date of July 23:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“I have received your last message regarding a survey flight from
                                    Alaska. “Our airplane B–25 will arrive in Nome sometime between
                                    the 8th and 10th of August and on leaving for the projected
                                    survey flight will take on board three American participants in
                                    the flight.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>Please accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>V. <hi rend="smallcaps">Molotov</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>